						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone lying on the tank bund about 2 miles from the village.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">18-19th century A.D.</hi> is a boundarystone of the field which was the <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> for the <hi rend="italic">gauḍike</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Guttaḷal,</hi> given to <hi rend="bold">Dēśāyi Hanumantagauḍa</hi> of Guttaḷal who belonged to <hi rend="bold">Mōnabhārgava</hi>-<hi rend="italic">gōtra</hi> <hi rend="bold">Kātyāyana</hi>-<hi rend="italic">sūtra</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Sukla-Yajuś</hi>-<hi rend="italic">śākhā.</hi></p>						

